20e%2Faccs%2C%20the%20world%20is%20simple%3A%20AI%20will%20solve%20our%20problems%20because%20we%20want%20it%20to%2C%20and%20we're%20the%20ones%20programming%20it.%20Opportunity%20is%20endless%2C%20and%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20AI%20rainbow%20is%20a%20singularity%20worth%20more%20than%20gold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20public%20proponent%20of%20Effective%20Accelerationism%20who%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20said%20that%20the%20movement%20wants%20people%20who%20can%20allocate%20capital%20to%20the%20e%2Facc%20cause%20and%20further%20their%20goals.%20He%20was%20granted%20anonymity%20to%20talk%20frankly%20about%20the%20movement%20without%20risk%20to%20his%20professional%20relationships%2C%20but%20his%20identity%20is%20known%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20proponents%20believe%20engineers%20will%20only%20invest%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftechno-optimism-silicon-valley-controversial-new-philosophy-marc-andreessen-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eevolution%20of%20AI%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20would%20benefit%20humans%20%E2%80%94%20but%20AI%20safety%20experts%20just%20don't%20see%20it%20that%20way%3B%20the%20e%2Facc%20movement%20has%20been%20heavily%20criticized%20%5Bby%20cyber%20security%20experts.%20One%20researcher%20called%20it%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F12%2F10%2Ftechnology%2Fai-acceleration.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DEffective%2520Accelerationism%2520(often%2520shortened%2520to%2Cbarred%2520pursuit%2520of%2520technological%2520progress.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ea%20dangerous%20unaccountable%20ideology%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20inspired%20by%20replacing%20humanity%20with%20AI.%26quot%3B%20Another%20said%20that%20the%20movement%20has%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Femilybaker-white%2F2023%2F12%2F01%2Fwho-is-basedbeffjezos-the-leader-of-effective-accelerationism-eacc%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eno%20social%20vision%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20a%20naive%20way%20of%20thinking%20about%20superintelligence%2C%20Roman%20Yampolskiy%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Cyber%20Security%20Laboratory%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Louisville%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%2C%20even%20in%20e%2Facc%2C%20will%20suggest%20that%20they%20have%20a%20working%20superintelligence%20control%20mechanism%20or%20even%20a%20prototype%20for%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20Yampolskiy%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhy%20would%20anyone%20think%20that%20it%20is%20possible%20to%20indefinitely%20control%20a%20superintelligent%20(god-like)%20machine%3F%20It%20is%20like%20thinking%20that%20squirrels%20can%20control%20humanity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYampolskiy%20is%20trying%20to%20warn%20the%20industry%20that%20the%20future%20of%20AI%20overlords%20that%20these%20e%2Faccs%20are%20quickly%20trying%20to%20usher%20in%20could%20be%20really%2C%20really%20bad.%20Terrifying%20even.%20And%20it's%20better%20to%20be%20safe%20than%20sorry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20years%20of%20research%2C%20e%2Faccs%20might%20see%20him%20and%20others%20invested%20in%20AI%20safety%20as%20a%20pessimistic%20doomer%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0or%2C%20in%20e%2Facc%20vernacular%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecel.%26quot%3B%20But%2C%20as%20Yampolskiy%20pointed%20out%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20many%20e%2Faccs%20are%20not%20scientists%20and%20are%20not%20AI%20safety%20researchers.%20This%20is%20his%20wheelhouse%20%E2%80%94%20not%20theirs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Either%20we%20stop%2C%20or%20we%20all%20die.'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20well-developed%20AI%20has%20the%20power%20to%20help%20screen%20for%20cancer%2C%20increase%20accessibility%20for%20disabled%20people%2C%20conserve%20wildlife%2C%20combat%20world%20hunger%2C%20and%20even%20aid%20in%20the%20climate%20crisis%2C%20critics%20of%20the%20e%2Facc%20movement%20argue%20the%20current%20practical%20applications%20of%20the%20technology%20would%20become%20immediately%20irrelevant%20should%20AI%20begin%20thinking%20for%20itself%20and%20determining%20its%20own%20goals%20for%20humanity's%20best%20interest%20without%20humans%20to%20control%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20e%2Faccs%20seek%20to%20defy%20the%20warnings%20of%20safety%20researchers%2C%20what%20about%20the%20rest%20of%20us%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EE%2Faccs%20want%20to%20reshape%20society%20radically%2C%20alter%20how%20we%20work%20and%20interact%2C%20and%20redefine%20what%20it%20means%20to%20be%20alive%2C%20but%20the%20general%20public%20doesn't%20have%20much%20of%20a%20say%20in%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20or%20enough%20money%20to%20have%20a%20voice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYampolskiy%20said%20that%20the%20attention%20this%20movement%20has%20garnered%20among%20the%20uber-rich%20is%20troubling%20and%20%26quot%3Beven%20more%20worrisome%20if%20you%20look%20closely%3B%20you%20realize%20that%20these%20people%20are%20not%20representative%20of%20humanity%2C%20our%20belief%20and%20values%2C%20they%20themselves%20are%20not%20value-aligned%20with%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20vision%20is%20diametrically%20opposed%20to%20that%20of%20the%20e%2Faccs%3A%20Pause%20the%20development%20of%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEither%20we%20stop%20before%20we%20get%20to%20superhuman%20AI%2C%20or%20we%20all%20die.%20'Huge%20AI%2C%20Inc.'%20should%20not%20be%20running%20dangerous%20experiments%20on%208%20billion%20humans.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feffective-accelerationism-humans-replaced-by-ai-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1703986774000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657cc9177a3c8094d5ddc2b9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feffective-accelerationism-humans-replaced-by-ai-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Silicon%20Valley's%20new%20ideological%20faction