0this%20has%20been%20an%20all-too-familiar%20scenario.%20The%20locals%E2%80%99%20name%20for%20the%20revered%20river%20is%20grim%20%E2%80%93%20Hungry%20Ganga.%20It%20has%20a%20voracious%20appetite%20for%20devouring%20hundreds%20of%20acres%20of%20cultivated%20land%20and%20settlements%20with%20each%20passing%20monsoon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENestled%20between%20the%20Ganga%20and%20the%20Fulahar%20rivers%2C%20Bhutni%20Char%20is%20a%20deltaic%20river%20island%20comprising%2063%20villages%20with%20a%20population%20of%20nearly%2090%2C000.%20The%20Ganga%20stretches%20expansively%20in%20this%20area%2C%20and%20even%20in%20early%20December%2C%20the%20opposite%20bank%20appears%20quite%20distant%20when%20you%20are%20on%20one%20side.%20The%20gap%20between%20the%20Ganga%20and%20the%20Fulahar%20is%20gradually%20decreasing.%20Just%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20distance%20between%20these%20rivers%20was%20around%202%20kilometres%2C%20now%20it%20has%20shrunk%20to%20a%20mere%20800%20metres.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30084225%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-9.07.39-PM-2.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30084225%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-9.07.39-PM-2.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30084225%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-9.07.39-PM-2-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F30084225%2FWhatsApp-Image-2023-12-08-at-9.07.39-PM-2-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691013%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Had%20the%20government%20paid%20more%20attention%20to%20river-bank%20erosion%2C%20we%20would%20have%20been%20spared%20of%20the%20struggle%20of%20resettling%20every%20other%20year.%E2%80%99%20The%20Ganga%20in%20Malda.%20Photo%3A%20Joydeep%20Sarkar%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20rivers%20look%20calm%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20but%20the%20soft%20soil%20remains%20vulnerable%20to%20erosion.%20Dhananjay%20Mandal%2C%20a%20longtime%20resident%20of%20this%20area%2C%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3Erecalls%20the%20river%E2%80%99s%20transformation%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20grandfather%20was%20around%2C%20the%20river%20was%20much%20smaller.%20However%2C%20since%202018%2C%20the%20Bhutni%20side%20of%20the%20riverbank%20has%20been%20eroding%20rapidly.%20We%E2%80%99re%20losing%20our%20land%2C%20but%20the%20question%20is%2C%20where%20can%20we%20go%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConstant%20losses%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flink.springer.com%2Farticle%2F10.1007%2Fs10668-022-02648-1%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOfficial%20data%20on%20land%20erosion%20in%20Malda%20district%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reveals%20significant%20losses%20along%20the%20Ganga%2C%20with%20approximately%2014%2C335%20hectares%20wiped%20out%20from%20the%20left%20bank%20between%201931%20and%201978%20and%20an%20additional%204%2C247%20hectares%20eroded%20from%201979%20to%202004.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20The%20constant%20shift%20of%20the%20Ganga%E2%80%99s%20course%20poses%20a%20yearly%20threat%20to%20a%20large%20chunk%20of%20land%2C%20with%20a%20substantial%20amount%20of%20it%2C%20totalling%20over%20200%20square%20kilometres%2C%20being%20lost%20due%20to%20bank%20erosion%2C%20impacting%20both%20the%20left%20and%20right%20banks%20of%20the%20river.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPeople%20live%20here%20in%20constant%20fear%20of%20losing%20their%20houses%2C%20made%20of%20thatch%2C%20mud%2C%20and%20bamboo.%20Many%20of%20them%20have%20been%20forced%20to%20move%20several%20times.%20When%20the%20monsoon%20season%20comes%2C%20they%20leave%20their%20homes%20on%20the%20banks%20and%20find%20safety%20in%20mainland%20areas.%20After%20the%20monsoon%20ends%2C%20they%20come%20back%20to%20these%20homes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%9CThe%20farmers%20and%20villagers%20in%20the%20area%20do%20not%20want%20to%20leave%20despite%20the%20crisis%20because%20the%20alluvial%20soil%20here%20is%20very%20fertile%20for%20cultivation.%20Just%20plow%20the%20land%2C%20and%20crops%20will%20grow%20without%20any%20fertilizer.%20However%2C%20the%20current%20crisis%20is%20unprecedented.%20The%20government%20needs%20to%20declare%20river%20erosion%20in%20this%20area%20as%20a%20national%20disaster%20and%20take%20action%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20farmer%20activist%20Biswanath%20Ghosh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMeasures%20taken%2C%20root%20cause%20ignored%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20area%20will%20be%20flooded%20again%20during%20the%20monsoon.%20We%20fear%20the%20worst%2C%20that%20it%20would%20be%20swallowed%20by%20the%20river.%20The%20sandbags%20meant%20for%20protecting%20the%20riverbank%20are%20not%20effective%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Rajesh%20Mahato%2C%20a%20resident%20of%20the%20area.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESneha%20Mondal%20was%20a%20child%20when%20she%20moved%20to%20the%20shelter%20at%20the%20local%20Birnagar%20School.%20She%20pointed%20to%20her%20one-time%20home%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20river.%20%E2%80%9CYou%20see%20the%20water%2C%20that%20where%20our%20house%20was%20located.%20The%20house%2C%20trees%2C%20shops%20%E2%80%93%20everything%20is%20gone.%20You%20can%20now%20see%20the%20crack%20in%20our%20shelter%20now%20%E2%80%93%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20where%20I%20will%20go%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(ma